This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques for human-machine interaction. The proposed AntNet model is specifically designed for reverse question answering, which falls under the category of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques for answer understanding, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The relevance-aware representation of answers and multi-hop based fusion are techniques that are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and semantic understanding (cs.SD). Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
